    <!-- The Lines of the Palm Section -->
    <section>
        <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-signature"></i> The Lines of the Palm</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <p>The lines on the palm are the most important aspect of palmistry. They reveal various aspects of a person’s life, character, and experiences. Below are the major lines found on most palms:</p>
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Heart Line:</strong> Represents emotional health, love life, and relationships. A deep heart line indicates a loving and compassionate nature, while a faint line may suggest emotional struggles.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Head Line:</strong> Represents intellect, thinking, and decision-making. A long and clear head line suggests clear thinking, while a short or broken line may indicate a scattered or indecisive mind.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Life Line:</strong> Represents a person’s general life path, vitality, and health. A long and deep life line suggests a strong vitality, while a shallow or broken line may indicate health challenges or sudden changes in life.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Mounts of the Palm Section -->
    <section>
        <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> The Mounts of the Palm</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <p>The mounts are the raised areas at the base of the fingers, which represent different characteristics associated with the planets. Here are the key mounts and their meanings:</p>
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Mount of Venus:</strong> Represents love, sensuality, and personal vitality. A well-developed Venus mount indicates passion and affection.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Mount of Jupiter:</strong> Represents ambition, leadership, and spirituality. A strong Jupiter mount suggests a person with leadership qualities and a desire to succeed.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Mount of Saturn:</strong> Represents wisdom, discipline, and responsibility. A pronounced Saturn mount indicates someone who is serious and reliable.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Mount of Apollo:</strong> Represents creativity, artistic ability, and success. A strong Apollo mount suggests a person with a flair for creativity and a desire for recognition.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Mount of Mercury:</strong> Represents communication, intelligence, and adaptability. A well-developed Mercury mount indicates strong communication skills.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Mount of Luna:</strong> Represents intuition, imagination, and emotional depth. A strong Luna mount suggests a person with deep emotional and intuitive abilities.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Fingers and Finger Shapes Section -->
    <section>
        <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-hand-point-right"></i> The Fingers and Their Shapes</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <p>In palmistry, the shape and length of the fingers also provide key insights into a person’s character. Here’s what each finger represents:</p>
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>The Thumb:</strong> Represents willpower and determination. A strong, well-formed thumb indicates a person with firm willpower, while a weak thumb may suggest indecisiveness.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>The Index Finger:</strong> Represents ambition and leadership qualities. A long, straight index finger suggests a confident, assertive personality.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>The Middle Finger:</strong> Represents responsibility and balance. A long middle finger indicates a responsible and grounded individual.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>The Ring Finger:</strong> Represents creativity and self-expression. A well-developed ring finger suggests a creative and expressive individual.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>The Little Finger:</strong> Represents communication and intelligence. A strong little finger indicates good communication skills, while a weak little finger may suggest social struggles.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Shapes of the Hands Section -->
    <section>
        <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-shapes"></i> The Shapes of the Hands</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <p>The shape of your hand, including the palms and fingers, also plays a crucial role in palmistry. There are four primary hand shapes, each corresponding to one of the four elements:</p>
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Earth Hands:</strong> Square palms with short fingers, representing a practical and grounded nature.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Air Hands:</strong> Square or rectangular palms with long fingers, indicating a thoughtful and intellectual personality.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Fire Hands:</strong> Square or rectangular palms with short fingers, representing an energetic and dynamic individual.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Water Hands:</strong> Long palms with long fingers, indicating a sensitive, intuitive, and empathetic personality.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Conclusion Section -->
